A video has emerged on social media of Hunt dancing to some house music with his player cheering him on. JOHANNESBURG Wits coach Gavin Hunt showed he had some moves following his team s clinching of the Premier Soccer League title.A video has emerged on social media of Hunt dancing to some house music with his players cheering him on.Known for his terse and short responses in his post-matches interviews, the overjoyed Hunt even went so far as to turn up the volume so that he can get down some more.He won his fourth PSL title, making him one of the most decorated coaches in South African football, equalling Gordon Igesund s record of winning four titles with different teams.Gavin Hunt got the moves 